    {
      "name": "Strategy Sync",
      "description": "Daily MetaApi → strategy stats sync pipeline. The cron fires at the configured `STRATEGY_SYNC_CRON` (default `5 0 * * *` UTC); these endpoints expose the same code path for ad-hoc operator use.\n\nConcurrency: the service holds a Postgres advisory lock for the duration of every run. Calling concurrently with the cron or with another invocation is safe — the second caller returns a `SyncRunResult` with `skippedReason: \"lock_held_by_other_replica\"` and never touches MetaApi or the database.\n\nHTTP semantics: both endpoints always return 200 (even on skipped runs). Operators distinguish \"ran\" vs \"skipped\" via the response body's `skippedReason` field. Possible values:\n- `no_account_configured` — `METAAPI_ACCOUNT_ID` env var missing.\n- `invalid_account_id` — env var is set but not a UUID.\n- `lock_held_by_other_replica` — another replica's run is in flight.\n\nAttribution: every MetaApi order must carry a comment of the form `<STRATEGY_COMMENT_PREFIX><lowercase-uuid>` (prefix defaults to `STRAT:`). Skipped deals are split into `dealsUntagged` (no recognisable prefix) and `dealsUnknownStrategy` (UUID doesn't match an active strategy) for operator triage.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Run Incremental Sync",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/strategy-sync/run",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "strategy-sync",
                "run"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Trigger an incremental sync immediately. Reads the per-account `sync_cursors` row to decide how far back to fetch:\n\n- **First run for the account** (no cursor row): backfills `STRATEGY_BACKFILL_DAYS` of history (default 365).\n- **Subsequent runs**: window is `[cursor.last_deal_synced_at − STRATEGY_SYNC_OVERLAP_MINUTES, now]` (default overlap = 60 min, to absorb clock skew between MetaApi and our wall clock).\n\nOn success, the cursor is advanced to the max `deal.time` observed during the run.\n\nResponse body: `SyncRunResult` with `dealsFetched`, `dealsAttributed`, `dealsUntagged`, `dealsUnknownStrategy`, `strategiesProcessed`, and `perStrategy[]` (per-strategy `tradesUpserted`, `snapshotWritten`, `error`)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Backfill Window",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"from\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"to\": \"2024-02-01T00:00:00.000Z\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/strategy-sync/backfill",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "strategy-sync",
                "backfill"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Re-pull a fixed historical window from MetaApi without advancing the cursor. Use after fixing a misconfigured `STRAT:<uuid>` comment on past orders, or when onboarding a new strategy and you need to re-attribute existing deals.\n\nBody (required, both ISO-8601):\n- `from` — inclusive lower bound of the deal-fetch window.\n- `to` — exclusive upper bound. Must be strictly greater than `from`.\n\nReturns the same `SyncRunResult` shape as `/strategy-sync/run`. The cursor is **not** touched, so subsequent normal runs continue from wherever they were before the backfill.\n\nErrors:\n- 400 — `from`/`to` not ISO-8601, or `from >= to`."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    }
